race.comment: Plenty of win chances. BIG STAR (7) has placed at two of three starts so far and resumed with a strong effort, trying to lead throughout but being run down late. That was first run from a long spell and will strip much fitter. Expected to take catching again. PRINCE OF POETRY (4) had one start as a juvenile and ran fourth of four but on the winner's heels. Jumping out well for return and should be much improved. Showed speed on debut and has a low draw. Stablemate MISS KASEI (9) has shown ability in four starts to date and was solid when resuming, beaten 3 lengths into fifth over 1000m at Mornington. Looks suited by the extra ground now.  MAYNARD (12) has finished sixth at both starts but not beaten far. Got much further back than expected latest but found the line strongly and has claims this line-up.
